race.description: Big Dance Day @ Muswellbrook 4 Nov Mdn Hcp
race.comment: VILLA CASTINA (3) opened this prep with a couple of minor placings at Hawkesbury, finding the line with purpose on each occasion. That earned her a crack at the Listed Dulcify last start and she wasn't disgraced, holding her position down the running to finish midfield. Looks better than these. VERITY (14) caught the eye on debut last start, coming from well back on the bend to get up for third over 1280m at this circuit. Gives every indication this extra trip will be right up her alley. Can race a bit closer this time and will be tough to hold out. MR CHIPS (7) appreciated the step up in distance when an eye-catching third last time out over 1400m at Scone. Drops 3kgs under today's scale and over a bit more ground looks a genuine contender. Market watch on BRILLIANT KINIGHT (1) first-up with blinkers on for the first time. GOLD CAPITAL (10) next best on a seven-day back-up.
